# [DTN](../wg/dtn.html)

## Summary

The Delay-Tolerant Networking (DTN) Working Group held its first session at IETF 126. The session focused on progressing core WG documents, evaluating individual security and utility proposals, and exploring solutions for IP-to-DTN edge gateway routing and reliability. 

Key advancements included stabilizing the CoAP over BP specification, plans for adopting the SAFE and BPv7 Echo Service drafts, and a consensus-backed rescope of the Bundle-in-Bundle Encapsulation (BIBE) work to deprecate RFC 9171 ADU fragmentation in favor of secure segmentation.

